{"title": "Ask HN: How Much a Difference Does an LLM's Corpus Make?", "link": "https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=48304669", "summary": "<p>That is, were I to omit all, say, novels and non-fiction from my LLM's training would then scientific questions be  better-addressed by that LLM vs another?<p>IOW is an LLM trained like a scientist indeed a better \"scientific\" LLM?</p>\n<hr />\n<p>Comments URL: <a href=\"https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=48304669\">https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=48304669</a></p>\n<p>Points: 1</p>\n<p># Comments: 0</p>", "published": "2026-05-28T04:53:09+00:00", "source": "Hacker News Best", "category": "techblog", "matched_entities": {}, "ontology": {"repo": "BlogRadar", "category": "techblog", "ontology_version": "0.1.0", "source_event_model": "blog_post", "event_model_id": "tech.blog_post", "evidence_policy_ids": ["source_metadata", "article_text"], "event_model_payload": {"headline": "Ask HN: How Much a Difference Does an LLM's Corpus Make?", "source_name": "Hacker News Best", "source_url": "https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=48304669", "published_at": "2026-05-28T04:53:09+00:00", "summary": "<p>That is, were I to omit all, say, novels and non-fiction from my LLM's training would then scientific questions be  better-addressed by that LLM vs another?<p>IOW is an LLM trained like a scientist indeed a better \"scientific\" LLM?</p>\n<hr />\n<p>Comments URL: <a href=\"https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=48304669\">https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=48304669</a></p>\n<p>Points: 1</p>\n<p># Comments: 0</p>"}}, "logged_at": "2026-05-28T05:09:28.965999+00:00"}
{"title": "Ask HN: Why not have an EU browser?", "link": "https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=48304668", "summary": "<p>I've been wondering, why don't we have a chrome fork that only accepts sites hosted in the EU? If a site is hosted in the EU then it can be fully regulated by the EU.<p>This would make it easier for citizens to know that their data is is safe (according to EU standards) and avoids the regulatory complexities of trying to enforce rules in other countries.<p>Thoughts?</p>\n<hr />\n<p>Comments URL: <a href=\"https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=48304668\">https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=48304668</a></p>\n<p>Points: 2</p>\n<p># Comments: 0</p>", "published": "2026-05-28T04:52:43+00:00", "source": "Hacker News Best", "category": "techblog", "matched_entities": {}, "ontology": {"repo": "BlogRadar", "category": "techblog", "ontology_version": "0.1.0", "source_event_model": "blog_post", "event_model_id": "tech.blog_post", "evidence_policy_ids": ["source_metadata", "article_text"], "event_model_payload": {"headline": "Ask HN: Why not have an EU browser?", "source_name": "Hacker News Best", "source_url": "https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=48304668", "published_at": "2026-05-28T04:52:43+00:00", "summary": "<p>I've been wondering, why don't we have a chrome fork that only accepts sites hosted in the EU? If a site is hosted in the EU then it can be fully regulated by the EU.<p>This would make it easier for citizens to know that their data is is safe (according to EU standards) and avoids the regulatory complexities of trying to enforce rules in other countries.<p>Thoughts?</p>\n<hr />\n<p>Comments URL: <a href=\"https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=48304668\">https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=48304668</a></p>\n<p>Points: 2</p>\n<p># Comments: 0</p>"}}, "logged_at": "2026-05-28T05:09:28.965999+00:00"}
